    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, in the 'spooky' version, there's no physical signal traveling between entangled particles. It's as if they have a shared secret that no one else knows. Physicists are still trying to understand this phenomenon, and there are a few theories that attempt to explain it. One idea is that entangled particles are connected through hidden variables that we haven't discovered yet, which would act like a secret code that determines their states. Another theory suggests that entanglement is a result of the particles interacting in such a way that their states become linked, and this link persists even when they are separated. It's like two dancers who have practiced together so well that they can still move in sync even when they're on opposite sides of the stage. The exact nature of the connection is still a mystery, and it's one of the most intriguing and debated topics in physics.",
