      "role": "user",
      "content": "the dancer thing is a good analogy but i'm still stuck on the \"spooky\" part. if there's no signal and no hidden code, it almost feels like there's some invisible force or something mischievous messing with the results. is there any part of quantum mechanics where things act like they're intentionally trying to mess with our measurements or break the rules?",
